CLAIM.OWNER: Loooch Racing Stables Inc and Hess Maria E

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL ASSCHER went up inside to press the pace, took a short lead on the turn, inched away and came out into the stretch, kicked clear under urging then steady handling late. GEMINI JOURNEY forced the pace four wide between horses then angled in and stalked inside on the turn, came out into the stretch and in upper stretch and bested the others. DEVIL'S BEAUTY dueled between horses then three deep on the turn, was fanned four wide into the stretch and outfinished a rival for the show. MYRCELLA a half step slow into stride, prompted the pace five wide, stalked outside on the turn, had the rider lose the whip a quarter mile out, came five wide into the stretch and was outfinished for a minor share. ZUZANNA angled in and saved ground chasing the pace, came out in midstretch and improved position. MAGICALCHIC saved ground stalking the pace on the backstretch and turn, continued inside in the stretch and did not rally. KRISTIE'S HEART chased outside then off the rail, came three wide into the stretch, steadied at the spill in upper stretch and lacked a rally. PEAKED settled outside a rival, split horses into the stretch and lacked a further response. BACK BEAUTY dueled inside rivals but a bit off the rail then between foes on the turn, lugged out leaving the turn and into the stretch, clipped heels when in very tight in upper stretch and fell but was walked off. The stewards conducted an inquiry into the spill in upper stretch before ruling no other runners were the cause of the trouble to BACK BEAUTY.
